      "a": "About $4.5B in federal contract obligations are recorded for Utah in FY2026 to date. Total obligations moved from $4B in FY21 to a peak of $7.2B in FY24, then declined to $5.2B in FY25 and to $4.5B in FY26. Award volume for FY2026 to date is 6,404 with an average award size of $700K, and obligations are down 14.1% year over year."
